# No Inline If

Always use block braces for `if`, `else`, and `else if`. Do not write a single statement on the same line or the next line without braces.

## Avoid

```javascript
if (x) return y;
if (ok) doSomething();
if (n > 0) continue;
if (done) clearInterval(id);
```

## Use Instead

```javascript
if (x) {
  return y;
}
if (ok) {
  doSomething();
}
if (n > 0) {
  continue;
}
if (done) {
  clearInterval(id);
}
```

This improves readability, reduces risk of bugs when adding lines later, and keeps style consistent.
